article.headline: New Hampshire 62, Towson 21
article.story:
TOWSON, Md. (AP) -- Ricky Santos threw for 413 yards and three
touchdowns and ran for two more as New Hampshire defeated Towson
62-21 on Saturday.

Santos completed 23 of 33 passes in his second career 400-yard
game and sixth over 300 yards. The Wildcats (2-0, 1-0 Atlantic-10)
gained 590 yards of total offense, including 152 yards receiving by
David Ball and 107 by Keith LeVan.

Towson (2-1, 0-1) set a school record for the most points
allowed in a home game. The Tigers gained 418 yards of total
offense, including 256 yards passing by Sean Schaefer.

The Wildcats took a 10-0 lead in the first 10:40, opening the
game with a seven-play, 80-yard drive capped by Santos' scramble
from 7 yards out. Connor McCormick then added a 19-yard field goal
to extend the lead.

On its next possession, Towson cut the lead to 10-7 when
Schaefer's 43-yard pass to Andrae Brown set up Nick Williams'
4-yard run with 2:30 left in the quarter.

New Hampshire answered with a 36-yard passing score from Santos
to Jonathan Williams and a 2-yard run up the middle by John McCoy,
and led 27-7 at the half.

Towson briefly cut into the lead again early in the third
quarter, with Schaefer's 31-yard pass to Rocky Brown, setting up a
10-yard touchdown pass to Marcus Lee.

But Corey Graham returned the kickoff 52 yards, setting up
Santos' second rushing touchdown, a 5-yard dash to extend the lead
to 34-14. Graham later added a 75-yard interception return for a
touchdown.
